## Limitations

The findings are based on available literature and public opinion, which may not encompass all perspectives or recent developments in the field. The complexity of juvenile delinquency means that conclusions drawn from these sources may not fully capture the nuances of individual cases. Additionally, the reliance on online sources may introduce bias, as not all viewpoints are equally represented in digital formats.